<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1166,1370]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1166,1191]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wings-pattern is similar to the next species. In the male genitalia, the central process of the gnathos in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,298,1203,1227]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemithyris">
<emphasis box="[151,298,1203,1227]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. hemithyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is shorter than half length of the uncus, but longer than half length of the uncus in 
<taxonomicName box="[1217,1331,1203,1227]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solealis">
<emphasis box="[1217,1331,1203,1227]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. solealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the base of the costa in 
<taxonomicName box="[316,463,1238,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemithyris">
<emphasis box="[316,463,1238,1263]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. hemithyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smooth, but slightly swollen in 
<taxonomicName box="[849,963,1238,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solealis">
<emphasis box="[849,963,1238,1263]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. solealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the saccus is shorter than in 
<taxonomicName box="[1295,1410,1238,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solealis">
<emphasis box="[1295,1410,1238,1263]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. solealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
